Both deliverables are written to the bundle directory:

- `transcript.json` — 25 iterations conforming to `transcript_schema.json`, each with self-contained hypotheses (named features, signed direction) and analyses recording effect estimates, p-values, and significance flags.
- `analysis_summary.txt` — narrative synthesis covering dominant main-effect predictors, the feature_038-by-marker interaction (treatment benefit confined to the triple-negative subgroup, +2.76 vs +0.03 months), null demographic findings (race / insurance), and the consolidated multivariable model (R² ≈ 0.90).

Key findings: feature_078 dominates (rho = 0.785), feature_057 / feature_051 / feature_038 are major; feature_038 benefit is heavily modified by feature_013, feature_043, feature_109 (all interaction p < 1e-50); race and insurance show no association with PFS, treatment receipt, or treatment benefit.
